cial to enable patient</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> with long-term conditions to be independent. </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">I</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">nformation creates informed patients, and informed patients experience better outcomes.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Of our patients surveyed last year (ACT), less than half (44%, 412/947) of patients reported that they had been provided with general epilepsy information from a health professional.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Only </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">half (50%, 472/947) of patients reported being given information about their medication and its effects from a health professional.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">I</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">nformation provision is </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">one easily addressable</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> area where the NHS, local authorities and Department of Health is not meeting expectations, and one where better signposting</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:'Fr